The paper proposes a fully-automated framework for segmenting left atrium in gadolinium-enhanced MR volumes using a customized 3D deep neural network. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of transfer learning and deep supervision strategies, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. The paper also mentions the use of a composite loss function, which is a technique used in neural network optimization and could be relevant to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with medical imaging, which could place it in the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
